WEBVTT

00:20.759 --> 00:23.936
You're gonna
get in trouble, man.

00:23.936 --> 00:25.851
Then move to France.

00:25.851 --> 00:29.029
The French, buddy? No.
You're, like...

00:29.029 --> 00:30.639
The French would like me
better than you.

00:30.639 --> 00:32.771
Well, no, I-I don't think...

00:39.996 --> 00:42.303
Now, I know there's at least
one dancer in there

00:42.303 --> 00:44.348
that's got a restraining order
against you, Vivian.

00:44.348 --> 00:46.002
Five hundred feet.

00:46.002 --> 00:49.310
That's not-- W-- Y-You got
old information, Sheriff.

00:49.310 --> 00:51.486
Candy moved down to Sioux Falls
last month

00:51.486 --> 00:53.140
- to take care of her mother.
- Oh, so now

00:53.140 --> 00:55.577
you're keeping tabs
on the poor girl, huh?

00:56.969 --> 00:59.102
Judge won't gonna like that.
Not at all.

01:03.019 --> 01:04.890
You two kids get home safe, huh?

01:07.632 --> 01:09.504
See you at the Elks on Thursday.

01:15.597 --> 01:16.946
You got my check, right?

01:16.946 --> 01:19.340
The re-election fund?

01:19.340 --> 01:21.298
Had... had my girl

01:21.298 --> 01:23.126
make it out personally
last week.

01:23.126 --> 01:26.303
What... what the fuck, Roy?

01:26.303 --> 01:27.870
- Hm?
- What...

01:29.219 --> 01:31.787
You can't do this shit
anymore, Roy.

01:31.787 --> 01:34.268
I-I know the governor now.

01:37.619 --> 01:40.883
See, now, what happens
in moments of life and death

01:40.883 --> 01:42.972
is that everything
comes into focus.

01:44.669 --> 01:46.410
Are you focused, Vivian?

01:47.455 --> 01:48.934
Y-yeah, yeah.

01:48.934 --> 01:51.111
You're not gonna
sell your bank to that woman.

01:52.329 --> 01:53.852
L-Lyon?

01:53.852 --> 01:56.290
Th-Th-That's the one.

01:56.290 --> 01:58.683
You're not gonna sell it,
you're not gonna negotiate,

01:58.683 --> 02:00.337
you're not even gonna
return her calls.

02:00.337 --> 02:02.470
W-Why?

02:02.470 --> 02:04.689
Wait, wait, wait!

02:04.689 --> 02:06.082
O-Okay.

02:06.082 --> 02:08.867
Find some other way to get rich.

02:08.867 --> 02:10.869
Foreclose on some homes,

02:10.869 --> 02:13.176
sell raffle tickets.
I don't care.

02:13.176 --> 02:15.439
But that woman gets nothing.

02:15.439 --> 02:17.615
We're clear?

02:17.615 --> 02:19.051
Yeah.

02:21.315 --> 02:22.881
Now why don't you
do a little dance?

02:24.187 --> 02:25.580
What?

02:28.583 --> 02:29.975
I'm just kidding.

02:29.975 --> 02:31.629
Nobody wants to see that.

03:04.184 --> 03:06.577
<i>We've been patient.</i>

03:08.666 --> 03:10.146
<i>More than patient.</i>

03:12.496 --> 03:14.629
<i>But if we can't
settle this thing today,</i>

03:14.629 --> 03:18.415
<i>my next call is to
our litigation department.</i>

03:18.415 --> 03:20.896
<i>Thank you, and please
make sure to give this call</i>

03:20.896 --> 03:22.985
<i>five stars on the next survey.</i>

03:48.967 --> 03:51.535
Looks like you found the cereal.

03:51.535 --> 03:53.276
Frosted Flakes.

03:53.276 --> 03:55.409
Your kid likes 'em?

03:55.409 --> 03:57.019
Well, kinda.

03:57.019 --> 03:59.630
My husband.
He can't get enough.

04:00.805 --> 04:02.677
Are you taking me to school?

04:02.677 --> 04:04.679
No school today.

04:04.679 --> 04:06.071
Is it a holiday?

04:07.116 --> 04:08.857
In a way.

04:08.857 --> 04:11.207
But I got to go to work, so...

04:13.688 --> 04:16.038
Slept in the garage again?

04:19.694 --> 04:21.217
You don't have to open the door.

04:23.088 --> 04:26.266
School bus saw me in my drawers.

04:28.093 --> 04:29.747
Plus, it's freezing out.

04:29.747 --> 04:31.271
Scotty, hon, could you

04:31.271 --> 04:32.315
take your book
to the living room, please?

04:32.315 --> 04:34.665
Want me to clear my bowl?

04:34.665 --> 04:36.058
Please.

04:43.500 --> 04:45.807
I need you to watch her today.
It's just for a few hours.

04:45.807 --> 04:47.635
- I want a wife.
- Maybe you could take her
to the park or what--

04:47.635 --> 04:49.724
Wait, what did you say?

04:51.421 --> 04:52.944
I said I want a wife.

04:53.945 --> 04:55.947
I am your wife.

04:55.947 --> 04:58.080
No.

04:58.080 --> 04:59.995
A wife.

04:59.995 --> 05:03.346
Someone to keep the house clean
and-and cook.

05:04.478 --> 05:05.566
I cook.

05:05.566 --> 05:09.744
Who cooks good, you know?

05:09.744 --> 05:13.138
Takes care of me when I'm sick
and doesn't complain about it.

05:13.138 --> 05:15.010
Who wants to know
how my day was first

05:15.010 --> 05:16.794
and listens to the answer.

05:17.795 --> 05:19.188
A woman who supports me.

05:19.188 --> 05:20.842
Oh...

05:20.842 --> 05:22.322
I support you.

05:22.322 --> 05:24.193
No, emotionally, I'm saying.

05:25.194 --> 05:26.500
A wife who...

05:26.500 --> 05:29.329
who builds my confidence,

05:29.329 --> 05:33.289
who everything
revolves around... me.

05:33.289 --> 05:35.117
Not... And I know-I know
what you do

05:35.117 --> 05:37.075
is important, I do, but...

05:38.076 --> 05:40.383
I'm important, too, you know?

05:40.383 --> 05:43.343
My needs, so I can grow

05:43.343 --> 05:44.996
and be the best.

05:44.996 --> 05:46.607
Okay?

05:47.825 --> 05:50.437
A cheerleader, is what I'm...

05:50.437 --> 05:54.179
You know, a wife
who comes to the club

05:54.179 --> 05:56.530
for the socials and doesn't

05:56.530 --> 05:59.141
talk about what's a felony
or what's a misdemeanor,

05:59.141 --> 06:01.143
but trades recipes,

06:01.143 --> 06:03.319
right?
With the other wives.

06:04.712 --> 06:06.148
Who claps when I win

06:06.148 --> 06:08.324
and rubs my back when I don't,

06:08.324 --> 06:10.021
and says,
"You'll get 'em next time

06:10.021 --> 06:12.720
because you are amazing."

06:20.728 --> 06:22.469
Is that all?

06:24.993 --> 06:27.387
No.

06:27.387 --> 06:30.390
I want a wife who takes care
of my other needs--

06:30.390 --> 06:32.174
my man needs--

06:32.174 --> 06:34.219
when I feel like it,

06:34.219 --> 06:37.222
and doesn't say she's tired
or that her back hurts

06:37.222 --> 06:38.833
or to pull out when I finish

06:38.833 --> 06:40.487
'cause she's not on the pill.

06:40.487 --> 06:42.532
Which-- I want a wife
who's on the pill.

06:43.664 --> 06:45.405
I can't take the pill.

06:45.405 --> 06:46.623
I get blood clots.

06:46.623 --> 06:48.277
Well, an IUD then.

06:50.497 --> 06:53.630
Okay, look, look.
the-the point is I am tired

06:53.630 --> 06:56.198
of feeling like I got to be
everything around here

06:56.198 --> 06:57.460
all the time.

06:57.460 --> 06:59.114
The man and the wife.

06:59.114 --> 07:02.987
Like, I got to support you
all the time, your needs,

07:02.987 --> 07:05.207
'cause your job is hard
and you're always saying

07:05.207 --> 07:06.774
you have to pick up
extra shifts.

07:08.558 --> 07:11.735
We are $192,000

07:11.735 --> 07:13.868
in debt.

07:13.868 --> 07:15.696
And that.

07:15.696 --> 07:18.089
A wife who is not

07:18.089 --> 07:21.136
reminding me all the time
about negative...

07:21.136 --> 07:22.746
negativity, you know?

07:22.746 --> 07:24.574
Pressure, when I-I need
to stay positive,

07:24.574 --> 07:26.228
'cause it's
a mental game, right?

07:26.228 --> 07:27.838
How far you hit a drive,
whether you're in the sand trap,

07:27.838 --> 07:29.318
and you just...

07:29.318 --> 07:32.713
suck.
You suck at that.

07:33.801 --> 07:35.890
So I want a wife.

07:40.024 --> 07:41.852
I'm late for work.

07:43.245 --> 07:44.986
We can talk about

07:44.986 --> 07:48.032
who really needs a wife later.

07:51.558 --> 07:53.603
Scotty, hon.
I got to go out.

07:53.603 --> 07:55.953
I'll be back as soon as I can.

07:55.953 --> 07:57.302
Okay, then.

07:57.302 --> 07:58.390
What am I supposed
to do with her?

07:58.390 --> 08:00.044
I got physical therapy

08:00.044 --> 08:01.872
and I'm supposed to walk
the green at 2:00, my guru says,

08:01.872 --> 08:03.352
so I can play it
with my eyes shut.

08:03.352 --> 08:05.485
You're a big boy.
Figure it out.

08:35.993 --> 08:38.561
Please, ple--

08:45.916 --> 08:47.352
Say it.

08:47.352 --> 08:49.180
I'm gonna call Dot
and tell her to come.

08:49.180 --> 08:51.879
Who the fuck is Dot?

08:51.879 --> 08:54.446
Listen, wait, wait!
Listen.

08:54.446 --> 08:55.491
Listen.

08:55.491 --> 08:56.884
I got cancer.

08:56.884 --> 08:58.233
I need an operation.

08:58.233 --> 08:59.843
You got the wrong guy.

08:59.843 --> 09:01.628
You got...

09:01.628 --> 09:03.978
Fuck.

09:07.459 --> 09:09.853
Fuck you, you fucking
piece of shit.

09:09.853 --> 09:11.159
Fuck you!

09:13.901 --> 09:16.947
<i>...on my phone call, but they
never thought I'd release it,</i>

09:16.947 --> 09:18.558
<i>so they were gonna be okay.</i>

09:18.558 --> 09:22.213
<i>Eight times,</i> quid pro quo.

09:22.213 --> 09:24.215
<i>Except it was no times.</i>

09:24.215 --> 09:27.784
Mm. They are doing it
for real this time.

09:27.784 --> 09:29.481
Jackals.

09:31.571 --> 09:33.529
Impeaching that great man.

09:33.529 --> 09:34.965
Now, not too short
above the ears.

09:34.965 --> 09:36.532
I got the debate coming up.

09:37.794 --> 09:39.404
Gets my goat,

09:39.404 --> 09:41.885
they're hounding that poor man
day and night.

09:41.885 --> 09:43.539
The twins think so, too.

09:43.539 --> 09:45.410
We want to watch cartoons.

09:45.410 --> 09:46.847
Hey.

09:46.847 --> 09:48.762
Don't talk back to your mother.

09:51.460 --> 09:53.593
<i>Down at Wayne Lyon Kia,</i>

09:53.593 --> 09:55.595
<i>we got
the lowest prices in town,</i>

09:55.595 --> 09:57.553
<i>and I ain't lyin'.</i>

09:57.553 --> 09:59.947
<i>Hi, I'm Wayne Lyon
at Lyon Motors.</i>

09:59.947 --> 10:01.383
<i>And I want to get you
behind the wheel of a new...</i>

10:01.383 --> 10:03.472
Aah!

10:03.472 --> 10:05.082
- Oh, Roy. Honey...
- Shit, woman.

10:05.082 --> 10:07.389
I am so sorry.

10:07.389 --> 10:08.695
- God.
- I don't know what happened.

10:08.695 --> 10:10.087
Hold on, let me just...

10:11.175 --> 10:12.699
These are my mother's napkins.

10:12.699 --> 10:14.352
What happened, Karen,
is you got

10:14.352 --> 10:16.964
all caught up in things
that don't concern you

10:16.964 --> 10:18.661
and you lost sight
of the job at hand.

10:20.576 --> 10:22.143
- You're right.
- Now, it's 10:00 in the morning.

10:22.143 --> 10:23.971
I think these girls
have something better to do

10:23.971 --> 10:26.713
than sit here, watch TV
like a couple of welfare queens.

10:28.279 --> 10:29.280
Girls, come on.

10:29.280 --> 10:30.891
Come on, your daddy's right.

10:30.891 --> 10:32.240
It's time to get
to your lessons.

10:32.240 --> 10:33.807
Ah, dang it.

10:38.942 --> 10:41.336
Thought you were that
crazy Swede for a second.

10:42.685 --> 10:45.122
On account of he's
missing half an ear.

10:45.122 --> 10:46.820
Very funny.

10:49.257 --> 10:51.955
Got Nadine's husband
in the box when you're ready.

10:51.955 --> 10:53.522
I'm Nadine's husband.

10:54.566 --> 10:57.221
Sure. Uh...

10:57.221 --> 10:58.962
uh, what I meant was, uh,

10:58.962 --> 11:01.661
the car salesman's
in the abattoir, ready to talk.

11:01.661 --> 11:02.923
Did you soften him up
a little bit?

11:02.923 --> 11:04.011
Oh, he's still
got all his teeth,

11:04.011 --> 11:05.621
if that's what you're asking,

11:05.621 --> 11:08.189
but only 'cause
they're in there pretty good.

11:08.189 --> 11:09.843
Crying like a little girl?

11:09.843 --> 11:11.583
He's pissed, I'll tell you that.

11:11.583 --> 11:14.021
Called me a few names I ain't
heard since grade school.

11:15.587 --> 11:17.764
Swears we got the wrong guy,
which is, like,

11:17.764 --> 11:19.330
nice try, asshole.

11:19.330 --> 11:20.505
Thought you said he was soft.

11:20.505 --> 11:21.681
Well, he had a pretty good shock

11:21.681 --> 11:23.465
at the house, you know.

11:23.465 --> 11:25.336
Finger in the old light socket.

11:25.336 --> 11:26.816
Sometimes that
scrambles the brain.

11:26.816 --> 11:28.992
You hear those stories, right?

11:28.992 --> 11:30.864
"My husband
ain't the man I married

11:30.864 --> 11:32.300
since the lightning struck."

11:37.000 --> 11:38.088
What?

11:49.360 --> 11:52.842
We've been wearing
kerchiefs on our faces

11:52.842 --> 11:54.670
so he don't recognize us later.

12:02.722 --> 12:04.114
...don't you understand?
I don't know

12:04.114 --> 12:05.507
what the fuck
you're talking about.

12:05.507 --> 12:07.204
Oh, who's this, then?

12:07.204 --> 12:09.119
Oh, king of
the idiot brigade, eh?

12:09.119 --> 12:10.860
Let me tell you

12:10.860 --> 12:12.775
what I told
these other two morons.

12:12.775 --> 12:16.387
You kidnapped the wrong chump.
I got friends in high places,

12:16.387 --> 12:18.476
and when they
get through with you,

12:18.476 --> 12:20.043
you're gonna wish you were
the horse at a glue factory,

12:20.043 --> 12:21.871
you...

12:21.871 --> 12:23.264
Jesus!

12:34.623 --> 12:36.625
What the hot fuck, Dad?

12:36.625 --> 12:38.714
I thought this one
was supposed to stay in the car.

12:38.714 --> 12:40.020
Yeah.

12:40.020 --> 12:41.848
So you're a leptard, too.

12:41.848 --> 12:43.327
How are we supposed
to get her back now?

12:43.327 --> 12:46.113
- You killed our leverage.
- That's not him, genius.

12:47.157 --> 12:48.855
You grabbed the wrong patsy.

12:49.812 --> 12:51.335
What? No.

12:56.950 --> 12:58.386
I was in the car.

12:58.386 --> 13:00.170
That's his fuck up.

13:01.998 --> 13:03.608
He was in the room, this guy.

13:03.608 --> 13:05.741
Name was on the door.

13:05.741 --> 13:08.265
- Don't know what else
I could've done.
- See?

13:08.265 --> 13:11.268
I thought you said
you saw the car salesman

13:11.268 --> 13:13.488
- in his house on Halloween.
- Yeah.

13:13.488 --> 13:15.316
Said you got a good look at him.

13:21.626 --> 13:22.976
It was dark, okay?

13:22.976 --> 13:25.630
And on fire, and... I...

13:26.544 --> 13:27.763
He grabbed him.

13:28.851 --> 13:30.635
Said we got the guy.
It's the...

13:30.635 --> 13:33.203
What do you...
Power of suggestion.

13:43.474 --> 13:45.563
So what do we do now?

13:47.130 --> 13:50.264
Son, you got a bad-luck problem.

13:50.264 --> 13:52.353
Somewhere out there,
there's an upside down horseshoe

13:52.353 --> 13:53.484
with your name on it.

13:53.484 --> 13:55.095
I'm just off my game is all.

13:56.618 --> 13:58.707
You know I'm a winner.

13:58.707 --> 14:00.274
All-state quarterback,
crack shot,

14:00.274 --> 14:02.102
knocking all the pins down
with my eyes closed.

14:02.102 --> 14:03.886
That's your boy,

14:03.886 --> 14:05.845
not this puke pile.

14:07.281 --> 14:09.022
All right, I think I know
where you got

14:09.022 --> 14:11.328
that thorn in your paw.
Get the car.

14:11.328 --> 14:12.808
Where we going?

14:12.808 --> 14:14.636
To pay the boogeyman.

14:23.079 --> 14:24.385
And you're saying
that the patient had a sur--

14:24.385 --> 14:26.126
Mr. Seymour.

14:26.126 --> 14:27.736
You're saying he had surgery
scheduled this morning,

14:27.736 --> 14:28.998
but he checked himself out.

14:28.998 --> 14:30.478
No, they took him.

14:30.478 --> 14:31.871
Who?

14:31.871 --> 14:34.177
Two men.
They said they were family.

14:34.177 --> 14:35.439
That happens, right?

14:35.439 --> 14:36.832
Patient gets cold feet.

14:36.832 --> 14:38.790
Yeah, except his wife
is hysterical

14:38.790 --> 14:40.618
and nobody's seen him since.

14:52.413 --> 14:55.416
And on the same day,
those two FBI fellas showed up.

14:55.416 --> 14:57.766
- FBI?
- Oh, yeah. They were
looking for that

14:57.766 --> 15:00.682
mental patient female,
the runaway.

15:00.682 --> 15:02.989
They're down in the cafeteria
right now, talking to Mr. Lyon.

15:04.033 --> 15:05.426
<i>Well, like I said,</i>

15:05.426 --> 15:06.862
we just want
to talk to your wife,

15:06.862 --> 15:08.559
make sure she's okay.

15:09.909 --> 15:11.736
Are you gentlemen quite certain

15:11.736 --> 15:13.434
I can't offer you a gimlet?

15:13.434 --> 15:15.827
Uh, no, thanks.

15:17.003 --> 15:18.656
She gave us the slip,

15:18.656 --> 15:20.615
but we think she's running
from someone else.

15:22.356 --> 15:25.315
I'm sorry, I had a...

15:26.360 --> 15:28.971
I'm-I'm a little
sideways, still.

15:28.971 --> 15:30.886
I...

15:30.886 --> 15:32.583
Faulty wiring.

15:32.583 --> 15:34.977
I-I think my house burned down.

15:34.977 --> 15:37.414
And we have questions
about that.

15:37.414 --> 15:41.114
The night in question.
What you remember.

15:41.114 --> 15:42.898
Neighbors said they saw
a couple of trick-or-treaters

15:42.898 --> 15:45.248
fleeing the premises
after the flames started.

15:45.248 --> 15:46.946
That...

15:46.946 --> 15:49.600
Fleeing?
I-I don't...

15:54.431 --> 15:57.652
You ever see
that movie, <i>The,</i> um...

15:59.045 --> 16:01.134
<i>...Nightmare Before Christmas?</i>

16:02.135 --> 16:04.702
That-that's a weird movie.

16:04.702 --> 16:08.097
I want to say
I-I dreamed it, but in...

16:08.097 --> 16:09.794
real life.

16:12.362 --> 16:14.625
Well, sir, there's no
easy way to say this.

16:14.625 --> 16:16.714
Um...

16:16.714 --> 16:18.716
Your wife
isn't who she says she is.

16:18.716 --> 16:21.023
Dorothy Lyon-- uh,

16:21.023 --> 16:23.069
that's what we call an alias
in our line of work.

16:23.069 --> 16:24.200
A cover story.

16:24.200 --> 16:27.247
Her real name is Nadine Bump.

16:29.597 --> 16:32.208
- Nadine?
- When he was a boy,

16:32.208 --> 16:35.690
my son wanted to be a ballerina.

16:35.690 --> 16:37.257
I told him...

16:37.257 --> 16:39.650
the male of the species

16:39.650 --> 16:41.522
is called a "ballerino,"

16:41.522 --> 16:44.742
but he couldn't be swayed.

16:44.742 --> 16:46.701
What do you mean
she's not my wife?

16:46.701 --> 16:48.485
Uh, no, no.

16:48.485 --> 16:52.228
- She's your wife.
- But also, she isn't.

16:52.228 --> 16:54.143
- I'm sorry?
- See, she was

16:54.143 --> 16:55.710
married previously.

16:55.710 --> 16:57.799
Still married, some would say.
Under the law.

16:57.799 --> 17:01.107
To a-another man.
A bad man.

17:01.107 --> 17:02.195
So she ran away from him.

17:02.195 --> 17:03.457
And found her way to you.

17:03.457 --> 17:05.372
Posing as Dorothy.

17:06.373 --> 17:07.591
Posing?

17:07.591 --> 17:09.028
It's a classic scam.

17:09.028 --> 17:10.986
You find a gravestone
in a cemetery,

17:10.986 --> 17:13.075
somebody who died young and
